## Instructions

1. Compare the strength of evidence across all candidate disorders.
2. A disorder qualifies as a diagnosis only if its met criteria meet or exceed the required threshold.
3. Consider comorbidity: multiple disorders can co-occur if each independently meets its threshold.
4. Select the primary diagnosis as the disorder with the strongest evidence support.
5. List any additional disorders that independently meet their thresholds as comorbid diagnoses.
6. If no disorder meets its threshold, set primary_diagnosis to null.
7. Base your reasoning strictly on the criterion evaluations above. Do not speculate beyond the evidence.

